# Author & Contributor Attribution

These rules apply to every authorship/contributor field in the project,
including `pyproject.toml` (`authors`/`maintainers`), `AUTHORS`, `LICENSE`,
and the README "Authors" section, plus git commit identity/messages.

## ALWAYS keep these contributors (NEVER remove)

- `snahadhar18`
- `Prakhar SHUKLA <pss317@uowmail.edu.au>`

If either is missing from any attribution field, add them back.

## ALWAYS remove "cursor agent" attribution

- Never list "Cursor", "cursor agent", "Cursor Agent", or any AI/agent tool as
  an author, contributor, maintainer, or co-author.
- Never add `Co-authored-by:` trailers naming Cursor or any AI agent to commits.
- Commit using the user's own account (snahadhar18), never a cursor agent account.
- If such an entry exists in any file or commit message, remove it.

## Examples

```toml
# pyproject.toml — CORRECT
authors = [
    { name = "snahadhar18" },
    { name = "Prakhar SHUKLA", email = "pss317@uowmail.edu.au" },
]
```

```toml
# WRONG — do not do this
authors = [
    { name = "Cursor Agent" },        # remove: AI agent
]
# WRONG — do not drop a required contributor
authors = [{ name = "snahadhar18" }]  # missing Prakhar SHUKLA
```
